captions.text:
It's Mary, and this week's
theme on Seven Gymnastics Girls

So I decided to show you
guys someone who inspires me

I've been a part of gymnastics
the last 16 years, 11 of which

So let's get started with
some tumbling skills.

What could be better than
tumbling with your coach?

It's great to have such
a supportive coach.

To encourage you
to do your best.

That was much
better, much better.
And even loves to have fun.

A good spot is really important
to learning a new skill.

Here are the shoutouts
from last week's video.

Thank you guys so much
for watching this video.

But before I go, I have
one question to ask Taylor.

What do you think
makes a good student?

I would say hardworking,
definitely, a very positive

Mary had [INAUDIBLE]
for that one too.
